## Step 2: iOS Compliance Scan (skip if `MOBILE_HAS_IOS=false`)

### 2.1 ŌĆö Guideline 2.5.2: Dynamic Code Execution (BLOCKER)

```bash
setopt +o nomatch 2>/dev/null || true  # zsh compat
# Patterns that violate 2.5.2
grep -rn "dlopen\|NSBundle.*load\|JSEvaluateScript\|evaluateJavaScript" \
  --include="*.swift" --include="*.m" --include="*.mm" . 2>/dev/null | head -20

# Custom OTA / hot-update patterns (non-Expo)
grep -rn "CodePush\|hot.*update\|ota.*update\|dynamicLoad" \
  --include="*.swift" --include="*.js" --include="*.ts" . 2>/dev/null | head -10
```

Flag any match as BLOCKER. Exception: `evaluateJavaScript` in a `WKWebView` loading
from the app's own bundle is acceptable ŌĆö flag for manual review, not auto-reject.

### 2.2 ŌĆö Privacy Manifest (BLOCKER for iOS 17+ submissions)

```bash
setopt +o nomatch 2>/dev/null || true  # zsh compat
# Check for PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy
find . -name "PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy" 2>/dev/null | head -5

# Check for Required Reason API usage (patterns that require manifest entries)
grep -rn "UserDefaults\|NSUserDefaults" --include="*.swift" . 2>/dev/null | wc -l
grep -rn "\.creationDate\|\.modificationDate\|attributesOfItem" --include="*.swift" . 2>/dev/null | wc -l
grep -rn "volumeAvailableCapacity\|volumeTotalCapacity" --include="*.swift" . 2>/dev/null | wc -l
```

If `PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy` not found AND any Required Reason APIs are used ŌåÆ BLOCKER.
AUTO-FIX: Create a minimal `PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy` template with the required categories.

### 2.3 ŌĆö Guideline 5.1.2: AI Data Disclosure (HIGH)

```bash
setopt +o nomatch 2>/dev/null || true  # zsh compat
# Check for AI SDK usage
grep -rn "openai\|anthropic\|claude\|gemini\|gpt\|ChatGPT\|LLM\|llm" \
  --include="*.swift" --include="*.js" --include="*.ts" --include="*.dart" \
  . 2>/dev/null | grep -v "test\|spec\|__mocks__" | head -20
```

If AI usage found: flag as HIGH ŌĆö requires disclosure in App Privacy section,
Privacy Policy, and in-app before first AI interaction.

### 2.4 ŌĆö Guideline 5.1.1: Permission Usage Descriptions (HIGH)

```bash
setopt +o nomatch 2>/dev/null || true  # zsh compat
# Read Info.plist
cat ios/*/Info.plist 2>/dev/null || find . -name "Info.plist" | head -3 | xargs cat 2>/dev/null

# Cross-reference: what permissions does the code use?
grep -rn "requestAccess\|requestAuthorization\|requestWhenInUse\|requestAlways\|AVCapture\|CLLocation\|CNContact\|PHPhoto\|HKHealth\|CBCentral\|requestPermissions" \
  --include="*.swift" . 2>/dev/null | head -20
```

For each permission used in code, verify the corresponding `NSXxxUsageDescription` key
exists in `Info.plist`. Missing keys ŌåÆ HIGH.
AUTO-FIX: Add missing `NSXxxUsageDescription` keys with placeholder descriptions ŌĆö
then AskUserQuestion to get the real user-facing text.

### 2.5 ŌĆö Guideline 4.0: Accessibility (HIGH)

```bash
setopt +o nomatch 2>/dev/null || true  # zsh compat
# Check for accessibility labels on interactive views
grep -rn "\.accessibilityLabel\|accessibilityIdentifier\|isAccessibilityElement" \
  --include="*.swift" . 2>/dev/null | wc -l

# Check for Dynamic Type support
grep -rn "preferredFont\|scaledFont\|adjustsFontForContentSizeCategory\|UIFontMetrics" \
  --include="*.swift" . 2>/dev/null | wc -l

# Flag hardcoded font sizes (not using Dynamic Type)
grep -rn "UIFont(name:.*size:\|UIFont.systemFont(ofSize:" --include="*.swift" . 2>/dev/null | head -10
```

Report count of accessibility labels and Dynamic Type usage. Flag hardcoded font sizes
for manual review.

### 2.6 ŌĆö Guideline 3.1.1: In-App Purchase Requirement (HIGH if applicable)

```bash
setopt +o nomatch 2>/dev/null || true  # zsh compat
# Check for third-party payment SDKs handling digital goods
grep -rn "Stripe\|Braintree\|PayPal\|Square\|RevenueCat.*purchase\|SKPayment" \
  --include="*.swift" . 2>/dev/null | head -10
```

If third-party payment found: flag as HIGH ŌĆö determine if it covers digital or physical goods.
StoreKit / Apple IAP required for digital goods/subscriptions.

### 2.7 ŌĆö App Completeness (MEDIUM)

```bash
setopt +o nomatch 2>/dev/null || true  # zsh compat
# Check for placeholder content
grep -rn "Lorem ipsum\|TODO\|FIXME\|placeholder\|stub screen" \
  --include="*.swift" --include="*.storyboard" --include="*.xib" . 2>/dev/null | head -10
```

